<div class="row">
  <div class="span4">
    <div class="news-column">
      <h3>Recent Announcements</h3>
      <br/>

      <%= scrape %> 

      <br/><br/>

      <%= link_to "Windows Store Launches", "http://www.wired.com/gadgetlab/2011/12/windows-8-store-introduced/" %>
      <br/><br/>
      <%= image_tag("https://encrypted-tbn2.google.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQeosI-n15HRsPYjrNmYJ-S6P6vqw6o85EJ0EmWvsvnzkJKTjdhmA", :border=>0, :class => 'dock-item') %>
      <p> To an installed base of 500 million-plus Windows users, the Windows Store presents a whole new world of software discovery and consumption. And to would-be app developers, the new platform splits the difference between the wild, woolly Android Market.
      </p>
      <br/>
      <%= link_to "Android Bouncer", "http://venturebeat.com/2012/02/02/android-malware-bouncer/" %>
      <br/><br/>
      <%= image_tag("http://venturebeat.files.wordpress.com/2012/02/bouncer-android.jpg?w=558&h=9999&crop=0", :border=>0, :class => 'dock-item') %>
      <p> Whether accurate or exaggerated, claims of rampant malware apps have haunted the Android Market. Now, Googleâ€™s Android team is announcing Bouncer, a new security mechanism that should prevent bad apps from ever making it into the Market. </p>
      <br/>
      <%= link_to "Apple Store App Promotion", "http://www.apple.com/itunes/25-billion-app-countdown/rules/" %>
      <br/> <br/>
      <%= image_tag("https://encrypted-tbn3.google.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSH3OevDsWHn4G09ASuw-IvV1vMYL8uaOpd224kld0S-C6SgZixzg", :border=>0, :class => 'dock-item') %>
      <p> The Apple store has reached 25 billion Apps and now is having 25 Billion Apps Countdown Promotion. </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="span4">
    <div class="news-column">
      <h3>Users</h3>
      <% User.all.each do |dev| %>
        <%= user_show(dev) %>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="span4">
    <div class="news-column">

      <h3>Recently Uploaded Apps</h3>
      <ul>
        <% App.all.each do |app| %>
        <li> 
          <a href="<%= app_url(app) %>" rel="tooltip" class="tooltipped" title="<%= app.name %>">
          <%= link_to app.name, app %>
          </a>
        </li> 
      <% end %>  
      </ul>      
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
